inn1.comm: the first ball is down leg side, Charles lets it pass. Lee's unhappy with that call because it may have clipped the thigh pad as the batsman let it go
this time the ball is wide outside off but isn't called, good pace and bounce off the pitch
Charles stays in his crease, gets behind the line and defends a good length ball towards point
defended on the off side

Lee roars a confident appeal for lbw but the umpire says not out. Australia decide not to review. Lee pitched in line and the ball went straight through to hit the pad. That was hitting high on middle and leg stump. Had Watson reviewed it, the umpire would have had to overturn his decision.
played through the off side and Charles scores his first international runs at home
played off the back foot towards cover
he too starts with a wide down leg side
pitches on a good length around off and the ball jags away from the right-hander, Barath watches it closely and shoulders arms
the ball leaves the right-hander off the pitch once again, good carry through to Wade
played back to the bowler
played off the back foot towards the leg side
width outside off stump and Barath stays in his crease and plays a flowing back-foot drive through cover, superbly timed
the ball pitches on a good length and seams and bounces sharply away from the right-hander, Barath gets squared up on the back foot and is beaten
Charles gets behind the line and defends on the leg side
full ball on middle stump, defended from the crease towards midwicket
Charles chases a wide ball outside off, throwing his bat at it, trying to blaze through cover. His footwork is poor and he gets beaten
good length and straight, Charles stays in his crease and blocks
Lee pitches on a good length around off and shapes the ball away from Charles, who stays in his crease and steers towards third man
that's full and wide down leg side, Wade leaps and makes a one-handed save
full ball outside off stump, Charles strides forward and shoulders arms, once again the carry to Wade is good
Charles has a careless waft at a good length ball that leaves him from just outside off, he is beaten
Hilfenhaus pitches in line with the stumps and begins to seam the ball away, Charles defends
a loud appeal for lbw but the umpire says not out and Australia do not review. The ball was full and Charles missed the flick, but that was missing leg
defended towards point from the crease
played towards cover point
pushed from the crease towards midwicket
Barath goes after a ball that is on the fuller side outside off, he opens the face as he plays a powerful square drive and places it through point
full length on a straighter line, Barath stays in his crease and flicks through midwicket, mid-on chases but can't prevent the boundary
a third consecutive boundary! Barath drives again, he was aiming for cover but sliced it in the air between two men in the point region, he went hard at the ball so it raced to the boundary
a slower ball on a good length, Barath gets behind the line and blocks
played firmly towards square leg for a single
Charles stays in his crease and plays to cover
Barath jumps back and across to defend a length ball that pitches around middle and off and begins to move away from the right-hander
short ball down leg side, Barath moves across and hooks, hitting the ball past Wade, just helping it along to the fine-leg boundary really
played crisply towards cover point, the ball is hitting the middle of Barath's bat, not so much for Charles
Barath moves across and closes his bat's face to play the fuller ball towards square
Charles stays in his crease and drives the ball towards mid-off
played off the back foot towards cover, where Michael Hussey fumbles to allow a single. That ball went straight to Hussey, a rare mistake from him
good length and straight, defended towards the bowler
short of a length outside off stump, Barath chooses to let it go
full ball on leg and middle, Barath stays in his crease and hits it off his pads in the air but to mid-on's left, well timed again
short and wide outside off, Barath reaches out for the ball and carves it over the in field at point with a powerful cut
good length and quick outside off stump, bounced sharply as well, Barath pushes from his crease away from his body and is beaten
driven to mid-off from the crease
Charles moves towards the line of the ball as it swerves away from him and steers towards third man
he's mis-timed this pull, it was not short enough and Barath ended up lobbing it over midwicket
that's bowled down leg side
good length and straight, Barath defends from his crease on the off side
played off the pads towards square leg
good length on middle and off, Barath once again moves across and defends with a straight bat

shot, Barath's simply lined up a full ball from Hilfenhaus and biffed it in the air past the bowler. The timing is splendid again. You can do that on this pitch, hit through the line. Barath plonked his foot forward and swung hard
good length on off stump, Charles stays in his crease and defends to point
Charles drives at the ball, trying to hit down the ground. He gets beaten. No where near as fluent as Barath, in terms of timing.
played off the back foot towards point again
Charles throws his bat off the front foot at a length ball outside off, he was aiming for cover but edged it towards third man, reached the fielder on the first bounce
Barath shows how it's done! He moves forward and towards the off, to get closer to the length ball, and simply drives through the line, hitting the ball in the air over cover
good length but wider outside off, Barath lets it go
a full ball down leg side, there have been a few such wides today
short of a length around off stump, defended on the back foot
Charles pushes from his crease and drives a length ball to mid-on
good length on middle and off, Charles stays in his crease and plays the ball back to McKay
good length and straight, played towards square leg
Charles tries to play towards the leg side but misses and is hit on the back leg, that was missing leg stump so no appeal from the bowler
Charles finally finds the gap and times the cover drive well. There was width outside off and he went hard at the ball, driving away from his body

caught behind! McKay, like he so often does, has picked up the wicket. The ball pitched on a good length just outside off and seamed away from the right-hander. It bounced a bit more as well. Barath stayed in his crease and prodded away from his body, getting a thick edge to Wade
Samuels moves back and across and shoulders arms to a good length ball outside off stump
fuller length outside off, Samuels drives from his crease towards mid-off
good length outside off stump, left alone by the batsman
short of a length outside off, Samuels watches it go past again
that's wide outside off stump, Samuels goes after it with a flamboyant front-foot cover drive, reaching far away from his body, he makes no contact
good length just outside off stump, Samuels plays off the back foot inside the line of the ball and gets beaten
length ball angling into the right-hander, played off the pads towards square leg
a full ball around middle stump, Samuels pushes from his crease towards mid-on, a similar ball trapped him lbw in the previous game, but that was on a slower pitch
defended from the crease towards the bowler
played off the front foot towards cover
length ball on the pads, played towards square leg
Samuels moves across and defends towards point
Charles takes a small step forward and drives the ball towards wide mid-on
good length with good bounce outside off stump, the batsman shoulders arms
good length outside off, Samuels chooses to play back and open the face to steer towards third man
pushed off the front foot towards cover
Charles drives at the ball from his crease and mid-times it towards cover, not very pretty, that shot
defended from the crease towards midwicket
driven off the front foot but to the bowler
pushed off the front foot towards point, Watson is keeping his regular wicket-to-wicket line
a half-volley outside off stump and Samuels uses the width to square drive through the gap at point, he came forward to play that shot
the ball rises from a good length and Samuels takes one hand off the bat while steering to third man
good length with bounce and a little seam away from the right-hander, Charles stays in his crease and hangs his bat outside off stump, he is beaten
good length on off stump, played back to the bowler
good length angling into Samuels who stays in his crease and defends on the leg side
driven from the crease with poor timing to cover
wider outside off stump, the batsman gets drawn out into driving to cover
good length outside off, Samuels defends from his crease on the off side
played off the back foot towards third man, the length was shorter outside off
short of a length outside off, played off the back foot in front of point for a single
full ball on the pads, flicked towards deep backward square leg

a huge appeal once again for lbw, and again Watson decides not to review the not-out decision. Charles was only a little forward and was hit high on the pad. Replays indicate the ball would have clipped the top of leg stump, but it wuld have stayed with the on-field call of not out
this time there was an inside edge on to the pad as Charles closed the face, Watson cut short his appeal

Charles tries to drive powerfully through the off side but ends up slashing the ball towards third man, the ball is about to go for a one-bounce four but Mckay slides along the boundary and saves runs
defended on the leg side
played from the crease towards point
defended back to the bowler from the crease
driven on the front foot towards mid-off
defended on the off side from the crease
so he can time the ball well then. Charles moves forward, gets under a length delivery and lofts through the line, hitting the ball cleanly over the bowler's head. Lovely shot
played from the crease in front of point
Samuels gets beaten by a good length ball that bounces a bit more outside off
on a length, outside off stump, squeezed away square on the drive
length ball, on the stumps and Charles pats the ball into the leg side
pitched up a little more and driven through a gap at cover to the sweeper on the boundary
full length, Samuels steps out and drives to mid-off - the batsmen think about a run but change their minds
back of a length, bouncing into the body, flicked round the corner for one
width outside off but Charles's flowing cut shot finds the man at point
on a length, seaming just a touch away, Samuels plays back, guiding the ball to short third man
pitched up but taking the pace off it, driven on the full to cover
probing line on or around off from McKay - Samuels leans forward to defend
touch short, gets a bit of bounce off the surface, the ball deflecting off Samuels glove and between his legs
length, drawing the batsman out, beating the outside edge
length ball outside off and Samuels shuffles across to leave this time - that's a maiden from McKay
length, on the stumps, tickled towards midwicket
pitched up and driven hard square - but David Warner shows his agility with a diving stop at point
tad shorter, the balls rears and Samuels block on front of his stumps
pitched up on the legs and clipped out to deep square this time
slightly back of a length, Charles stays back and is beaten outside off as he fished from the crease
fuller ball, driven to cover
good length, outside off, played square into the off side from the crease
slightly fuller and Samuels leans out to push the ball behind point - plenty of time for them to run a couple as long leg comes round
length, outside off and driven to mid-off
back of a length, Samuels moves across in front of his stumps and dabs to short third man
pitched up, driven to mid-off - not the cleanest of connections from the batsman

the lights finally go out for Samuels! The watching world can sleep easy ... Lee fizzed one through, Samuels fenced and got the thinnest of nicks through to Wade. I can't see that disappointing the crowd too much - a scratchy innings has scratched its last
flighted, on the stumps, nudged square on the leg side
tossed up outside off, spinning back as Bravo leaves - didn't quite turn enough but it brought gasps from the attendant Aussies
pushed across, defended on the front foot outside off
flighted across the left-hander again, driven to mid-off
fullish and Charles steps out to sweep powerfully to the deep backward square boundary
tossed up on the stumps and Charles paddles this one even finer - though this time there's a man in place to rein it in
quick bumper from Lee, rising sharply on the batsman, who does well to get on top of it
pitches this one up, sliding across Bravo ... who shoulders arms as the ball whistles through to the keeper
full, guided behind square on the off side
pitched up outside off, Charles stands and thumps cross-batted to mid-on, who dives to cut it off
just a little short from Lee and Charles seizes on it, whipping his arms through a pull shot that flies over midwicket and hard away to the boundary
this time Charles swings through the off side - he's coming out of his shell. Lee doesn't look to pleased about it
tad short from Doherty, Bravo cuts through a gap in the covers
tossed up, defended outside off stump
flatter, quicker, Bravo again plays a forward defensive on the stumps
flighted, knocked back to the bowler on the back foot
tossed up outside off and pushed to the man at extra-cover
flatter, again sliding across, cut away to the deep square boundary
loses his line down the leg side - not the best start
slightly short, angled across, cut to point
length, on the stumps, prodded short on the off side
almost a full toss, wide of off stumps and Bravo opens the face, guiding the ball off the toe of the bat down to third man
defended coming forward in front of the stumps
length, on the stumps, defended square on the off side
line and length for Hilfenhaus, with Bravo sitting back to blocking to point
on the stumps, flighted, straightening a touch, and defended

the St Lucia crowd falls silent: Charles has holed out to long-on. It was a length ball and Charles skipped out eagerly to meet it but his slog didn't quite come off the middle - the ball ending up in Brett Lee's middle as he took a jumping catch on the boundary

Dwayne Bravo faces a review first ball ... and he's gone! Doherty tossed one up around leg stump, Bravo leaned forward with his bat against his pad. The ball thunked just below the knee roll - and replays showed it would have gone on to break the wicket. That's two in two for Doughy!
flat delivery, given a rip, but Pollard turns the hat-trick ball off his pads
flighted, outside off and just misses the outside edge as Pollard attempts to cut
defended in front of the stumps by the big man
drops slightly shot, Bravo plays the ball towards cover off the back foot
length, on off and Bravo steps out to defend
length, driven towards cover and again no run
shorter ball, played off the back foot out to point
angled across, around off stump, Bravo pushes square towards point again
pitched up and this time Bravo finds the gap, lacerating a drive to the backward point boundary
floated up around off, Pollard defends
length, on off, still no bite from Pollard, who defends back to the bowler
full, on the stumps and this time Pollard heaves the ball back down the ground - he hit that straight and hard to beat long-on
on off stump, Pollard plays back
on the stumps, defended coming forward
tossed up and clipped to midwicket
short, defended into the off side
back of a length, Bravo sits in his crease and defends towards point
length ball, angled across, defended into the covers
nagging line and length, Bravo steps out and plays the ball square
drops short and Bravo rides the bounce, cutting hard past the dive of extra-cover
Pollard ducks under a bumper - and it's called on height
length, on the stumps, nudged into the on side
again Pollard goes down the ground, picking Doherty up from around off stump and smacking him to straight-ish long-on
tossed up, defended on off stump
flatter, width for Pollard, who slashes the ball away behind point
length, defended back to the bowler
full length, Pollard presses forward and blocks
drags the length back, slight turn, clipped back to the bowler
length, angled outside off and dabbed to point
metronomic attack from Hilfenhaus - this time Bravo manages to flick him through gully for one
tight off-stump line, Pollard defends standing back in his crease
slightly short and hooked, though off the splice - still went quite a long way towards deep midwicket
pitched up on the pads and glanced to long leg, who makes a tumbling stop
bouncer and Pollard genuflects to let it pass over his head
flighted, from left to right, driven hard from outside off to the deep cover boundary
on the stumps, nudged into the leg side
tossed up, Bravo leans round his pad and dabs to midwicket
flighted, forward defensive from Bravo
drags it shorter, Bravo goes back and punches down the wicket
on the legs, worked round the corner
length, angled across, pushed towards cover
slightly fuller, Bravo steps forward and blocks
turned into the leg side off a good length
tight line, defended back to the bowler
immaculate line and length, Bravo gets solidly behind it
finally a bit of room outside off and Bravo cuts to the sweeper at backward point
cut hard off the back foot towards deep point, where Forrest covers a lot of ground and slides to prevent the boundary
pushed off the front foot towards point
bowled flat and quicker from round the wicket, Pollard stays back and plays towards the bowler
defended on the front foot
Pollard steps out of his crease but isn't to the pitch of the ball and has to defend
that's too short and Pollard has hammered it, going back in a flash to pull with power, he's hit it flat but so hard that it's carried over the boundary rope
good length outside off stump, driven from the crease towards long off
Pollard tries to turn the ball on the leg side but it bounces sharply from a good length and it lobs off the leading edge towards the off side, Pollard took one hand off the bat as he played that
defended from the crease on the leg side
Bravo pushes away from his body at a length ball that angles across him and punches towards short cover, the ball was hit in the air but fell just short of the fielder
short of a length delivery angling across the left-hander, Bravo stays back and steers towards backward point
good length and straight, Bravo defends on the off side
Watson beats Pollard by pitching just short of a length and getting the ball to bounce and straighten off the pitch

Watson appeals but the umpire says not out. Pollard stayed back and was hit on the top of the front pad by one that angled into him, possibly too high. Replays indicate the ball would have only just clipped the bails so that would have been an on-field call
defended on the front foot

Bravo's been caught! He drove hard at a length ball angling across him, playing away from his body, trying to hit on the up and through the line. He ended up slicing it high in the air towards the edge of the circle at cover. There was a fielder steaming in from the deep but David Hussey ran back from the in-field to take a well-judged catch
defended on the front foot towards the bowler
played from the crease towards the off side
Lee tests the batsman with the quick bouncer, Russell has to duck in a hurry
short of a length at the body, Russell stays in his crease and plays towards midwicket
good length and straight, Russell gets behind the line and defends
length delivery just outside off, played from the crease towards point
short ball that rises rapidly outside off stump, Russell fends at it, trying to steer to third man, but is beaten
driven from the crease towards mid-off, the shot is mis-timed and the fielder is on the edge of the circle, so a single is available
he was nearly bowled there, Russell backed away to cut a length ball outside off and was beaten close to off stump
pushed from the crease with an angled bat to play the ball to third man

Pollard comes down the pitch but then gets hit in the mid-section by a short of a length ball, the ball goes on the off side and Pollard wants one, but the fielder at point is quick to charge in and prevent the single
dropped at his feet for a risky single, Russell responds quickly and sprints towards the danger end, beating Watson's sprint, clean pick-up and dive to break the stumps
Russel swings at a good length ball out side off and is beaten
defended on the back foot towards the bowler, Watson is bowling an impeccable line and length

Pollard backs away and pulls the ball into the empty space between midwicket and deep midwicket, David Hussey ran back from the circle, sprinting towards the outfield, and dived full length to try and catch the ball as it dropped over his head, it was just out of reach
played on the leg side for a single

he's carted that for four over point! Russell cleared his front foot out of the way towards leg side, and was facing the short ball outside off square on, he flayed his bat, freeing his powerful arms and using the width on offer, slashing the ball for a one-bounce four, that almost carried for six
played towards midwicket for a single
played off the hips through square leg
short of a length delivery at the body, fended down towards square leg on the back foot
a rare mistake in line from Watson, this one is down leg side
Pollard has blasted the length ball from around off stump over the long-off boundary. He stood in his crease and simply hit through the line with immense power
played from the crease towards point for a single
Russel stays in his crease, gets down low and opens the face of his bat to steer the full ball from outside off between backward point and short third man
and Russell gives the fielder at third man work to do by cutting a length ball
Short of a length but it's on the pads, Pollard glances the ball firmly and beats the diving fielder at short fine leg. Watson's figures have been ruined.
defended on the front foot. Watson has more than doubled the number of runs he's conceded
Russell gets down on one knee and sweeps powerfully into the gap on the square leg boundary
played off the back foot and he's placed it behind point, the fielder has some chasing to do
bowled quickly into the right-hander, dabbed off the pads towards square leg
driven firmly towards long-on
a full toss and Russell will feel he missed out, he hit it back to the bowler
pushed from the crease into the gap at cover
short of a length ball, the batsman stays back and swivels to pull the ball along the ground to deep square leg
a full ball on the pads, flicked powerfully to the fielder at deep square leg
a slower short ball, Russell pulls but can't beat Doherty at short fine leg
nearly in the blockhole, Pollard stays in his crease and forces the ball towards long-on
dabbed off the back foot towards square leg
tries to flick a one that's nearly in the blockhole off his pads but doesn't make proper contact
mis-timed back to the bowler, Pollard was trying to hit that a bit too hard
driven on the front foot to long-on
Pollard's tried to whack that down the ground, Doherty bowls a fast and flat ball and induces a mis-hit on the off side
fired into the blockhole, the batsman digs it out towards cover
Pollard gets to his half-century by whacking Doherty flat over his head, nearly went all the way too, bounced just inside the boundary. That's the first fifty for West Indies in the series
driven hard and straight once again but the fielder in the deep cuts it off
Pollard backs away towards leg and uses the room he's created to drive a full ball with power through extra cover
played off the back foot with an open face to third man
a slower ball and the batsman pulls to early, mis-timing it on the off side when he was trying to hit towards leg
a yorker this time, the batsman manages to keep it out and run a quick single
full and straight, Russell drives straight past the bowler, David Hussey runs to his right from long-off to cut off the ball

Forrest has mis-judged the catch on the backward square leg boundary and conceded six! Pollard flicked the ball off his pads in the air, Forrest moved to his right on the boundary and wasn't sure where the boundary was. In the end the ball went past him and bounced beyond the rope
played through square leg
Pollard has heaved at this ball and I thought it was going straight up in the air, because he looked like he mis-hit it. But it's fallen over the boundary at long-on. Incredible power.
played to deep midwicket for a single
Russel clears his front foot and slogs through square leg
good length and straight, we haven't seen a front foot defence in a while. Pollard plays the ball down the pitch and Russell sets off, Pollard sends him back in time
he's teed off here. Watson bowls a full ball and Pollard swings so hard, launching the ball miles over the deep midwicket boundary, tremendous hitting. This total could spiral towards 300 quickly
the slower ball but it is too wide outside off stump
dabbed off the back foot towards third man
dropped by Doherty at short fine leg. Pollard flicked the ball straight off his pads and straight to the fielder in the circle. That's a sitter. McKay looks rather upset
played towards long on for a single
Pollard backs away towards leg and swings hard, this time he is beaten by the slower ball outside off
a full ball in the blockhole, Pollard backs away and drives to long-on
Russell swings across the line with power, sending a length ball racing towards deep midwicket
that's not that short but Russell is waiting, ready to pull, he heaves it with tremendous power for a one-bounce for to deep midwicket

caught at extra cover! Watson bowled a full ball outside off stump, Russell stayed in his crease and drove hard, he made good contact, hitting the ball well but in the air towards Bailey, who took the catch to his left
drives his first ball towards long-off for a single
a full ball outside off, nearly in the blockhole, Pollard reaches out and plays it towards backward point
nudged off the back foot towards deep backward square
a full ball swinging into the blockhole, driven towards long on for a single

that's been caught, and then dropped. Pollard hit the ball high in the air towards deep backward square, Forrest judged the catch superbly and caught it with his back foot a centimetre from the boundary rope. He then held the ball for a second or two before beginning to lose his balance and go over the rope. So he tossed the ball back in. However, the umpire wants to check if Forrest was stepping on the rope as he caught the ball. It's a close call, and eventually the umpire signals six
driven down the ground to long off
played off the back foot towards third man
watch out in the stands beyond deep midwicket! McKay's back of the hand slower ball is too short and it sits up for Pollard, who wallops it flat over the boundary with a powerful pull
driven with power to long on for a single
driven to long of for another single
full ball outside off, Sammy drives with power this time, finding the gap on the deep cover boundary
too full on the pads this time, Sammy flicks, and flicks superbly into the gap on the backward square leg boundary
defended back to the bowler
driven to long-on for a single
hit flat and hard towards long-off, Warner runs in to try and catch the ball, then decides to stay back and field it, it bounces into his chest
driven firmly through the off side for a single
short ball and Sammy pulls towards deep square leg
Pollard gets to his century with a huge hit over the midwicket boundary, backing away to a short delivery and pulling, he takes of his helmet and roars, tremendous intensity in that celebration

he's gone this time, the delivery was fuller outside off and Pollard swung hard at it, slicing it in the air towards deep cover where Hussey ran in and took the catch. Pollard's played a special innings and he gets a warm ovation from this crowd
Sammy's pulled a short ball and what's happened there? The ball went high in the air and cleared Forrest on the boundary. He's not having much joy out there
Full ball outside off stump, Sammy stays in his crease and drives hard, drilling the ball past Lee and beating the fielder at mid-off

Sammy's ended the innings with what could be the biggest hit of the day! He's sent the length ball flying over the midwicket boundary with an immense swing. West Indies have scored 145 runs off the last 12 overs to finish with 294. Sammy raised his fist as he watched that ball disappear from sight

inn2.comm: the ball lifts from short of a length and angles into Watson, who plays from his crease and gets hit in the stomach
played off the back foot towards third man
a full ball crashes into Warner's back pad after he misses the flick, Roach appeals but that pitched outside leg
defended on the back foot towards the bowler
short of a length and straight, played off the back foot on the leg side
a full delivery outside off stump, Watson tries to steer through point but misses
Bravo goes down leg side with his first ball from over the wicket to the left-hander

caught at mid-on! Warner stays in his crease and tries to loft off his pads, he ends up spooning it in the air to Narine. The length wasn't full enough for that shot and he was through his shot too early. An ideal start for West Indies
Watson strides out and tries to drive through cover, ends up mis-timing it on the leg side
Forrest's first ball is a bouncer but it is too high
good length and straight, Forrest gets behind the line and defends
too full and on the pads, flicked towards square leg
too full on the pads, Forrest gets going with a crisp flick, placed into the gap on the deep square leg boundary
good length and straight, defended on the leg side
full and straight, Watson moves forward and drives towards the bowler, Roach raises his hand and deflects the ball towards mid-off
defended from the crease on the off side
short of a length outside off, steered off the back foot towards third man
cut off the back foot towards deep point
short of a length outside off, lofts of lift for Roach, Forrest lets it go
fuller length and a bit too straight, Forrest clips off his pads and finds the boundary behind square again
good length outside off stump, defended on the off side
a full ball angling into the right-hander, Watson tries to flick but misses and is hit on the pad, that was missing leg stump
too full and too wide, Watson strides forward and plays a powerful drive through extra cover, he hit it in the air but past the diving fielder
nudged off the pads towards wide mid-on
short and extremely wide outside off, he's going to have to bowl that again
Forrest moves across his crease and flicks the ball through square
Watson strides forward to a length ball and hoists it back over the bowler's head with a powerful drive, superb shot, clinically executed
short of a length but down leg side, another wide. Australia also had this leg-side wide problem early when they were bowling
good length outside off stump, Forrest stays in his crease and tries to defend, he gets beaten
short of a length outside off, good carry to the keeper after Forrest shoulders arms
good length angling into the right-hander, played from the crease on the leg side
Forrest jams down on a length ball outside off and gets a bottom edge past his stumps on the leg side, he hit that with the inside toe of the bat
Watson strides forward and drives but doesn't beat cover
too short, Watson swivels and dispatches the ball into the stands at midwicket with a powerful pull, he's got this chase started
played off the back foot through cover
edged and just wide of the diving Baugh! There's no slip in place. Watson tried to run a good length ball that angled into him towards third man and edged it finer than he would have liked
defended on the front foot on the off side
is that another edge? It was! Watson tried to steer to third man once again and the ball bounced off the outside edge, Baugh dived full length and got some glove on it but could not hold on.
defended on the leg side
Bravo bowls another full ball down leg side
short ball and Forrest pulls towards deep square leg
short of a length angling into the body, played off the back foot through midwicket
short of a length around off stump, defended on the back foot
Forrest stays in his crease, waits for the length ball and drives through the line, placing it perfectly between the bowler and mid-off
defended from the crease towards mid-on
good length outside off stump, Forrest strides forward and shoulders arms
another outside edge races to the third man boundary. This time along the ground and wide of first slip. Forrest pushed forward to defend but edged it
Watson moves forward to defend, he gets hit on the pad and the ball lobs up in front of him, Baugh runs forward to catch it, no bat on that though
Watson tries to defend on the back foot but gets an inside edge on to his pad
defended on the back foot towards square leg
Watson strides forward and plays on the leg side
played off the back foot in front of square
defended on the back foot on the leg side
Watson's holed out to mid-on! He saw the ball was short and went to pull, he hit it from outside off and played the shot too early, slicing it high towards Roach who took the catch inside the circle.
good length outside off stump, Bailey stays back and plays to point
played off the back foot wide of short third man for a single
fuller length around off stump, Forrest pushes on the front foot to mid-off
short ball, Bailey swivels and swats it into the gap on the deep backward square leg boundary, he was in total control of that shot and timed it well enough to beat Russell
left alone outside off stump
defended on the back foot
played off the front foot to Pollard at midwicket
defended towards Pollard at midwicket again
pushed off the front foot towards deep midwicket
spin from outside off into the right-hander, Bailey defends on the back foot
Bailey defends once again, Narine's exceptional economy continues

Forrest's been caught at third man but the fielder, Johnson Charles seems to have hurt himself. Forrest tried to hook a short of a length ball but ended up top-edging it towards third man, Charles came running in from the boundary and dived forward, taking the catch inches from the ground. Splendid effort. But he hit his shoulder hard as he caught the ball and is in some discomfort. He doesn't celebrate his catch too much and the physio is tending to him
good length and straight, played back to the bowler
short of a length on the hips, Hussey moves across and glances behind square
defended on the off side
played off the back foot behind point
Hussey goes back and taps the ball towards square leg
Hussey goes back and cuts towards deep backward point
Bailey moves forward and pushes the ball towards long on
Hussey strides forward to defend and gets beaten by one that spins across him
Narine appeals for lbw but the umpire says not out. Hussey went back and across to a skiddy ball and tried to play towards square leg. That pitched outside leg. West Indies do not review.
driven firmly off the front foot towards deep point
driven off the front foot towards long off
a length ball which Hussey plays back to the bowler
played off the front foot towards wide mid-on
Bailey clips the ball off his pads towards deep backward square
Hussey strides forward and drives to cover
length ball outside off, Hussey moves forward and drives to short cover
good length and straight, Hussey gets behind the line and defends solidly
driven off the front foot to mid-off
good length, angling into the right-hander, defended on the off side
another full ball angling into Bailey, who leans across and drives to mid-on, there's a mix-up in the calls but they run in the end
played from the crease towards gully, where Sammy dives to his left and fields
Bravo strays down leg side
fuller length outside off stump, Hussey lets it go as the ball slides across him
terrific shot! Hussey's so good in that region. He had width to cut, because the ball was short and wide, and he placed it between gully and backward point, third man had no chance either
good length and straight, Bailey defends
good length on a wicket to wicket line, Bailey defends towards the bowler
short of a length outside off, Bailey steers to third man where Bishoo, who's on the field for Charles, fields
Sammy angles the ball back into the left-hander after slanting it across him, Hussey bottom-edges the cut on to his pad
defended towards point
driven from the crease towards cover
touch back of a length, spearing in, Bailey hops back and deflects the ball to midwicket
slanted across the lefty, on a good length, dabbed to third man
down the leg side, Bailey can't get anything on it
length ball, defended in front of the stumps back down the wicket
fuller ball, on the stumps, worked to mid-on
back of a length, Bailey goes back and drives to short cover

full, straight, driven back - and the ball hits the stumps at the non-striker's end. Roach couldn't get a fingertip on it, but they decide against running on the deflection ... then a wild throw from sub fielder Devendra Bishoo at mid-off hands them a single to long leg anyway
Good length ball outside off, Bailey pushes forward and opens the face to steer towards third man
Good length around middle and off, Hussey pushes off the front foot to mid-off and runs quickly
Bailey moves forward to a length ball and simply hits through the line, a pick-up shot that sends the ball over the wide-long on boundary, didn't look to hit with much power, just timed it
left alone outside off stump
Bailey gets an inside edge on to the pad towards square leg
there's width to cut and Hussey loves it there, cracking it past gully into the gap on the third man boundary
short ball and Bailey plays the swivel pull to the deep midwicket boundary
Dwayne Bravo leaps to his left at extra cover to cut off a firmly-hit drive, saved three runs I think
Hussey tries to cover drive but mis-times it towards mid-off
turned off the pads through square leg
too full outside off, Hussey moves forward and uses the width to free his arms, drilling the ball through cover with a powerful drive
too straight this time, Hussey clips off his pads to square leg
length ball on middle and off, Hussey pushes from his crease in front of point
fuller length on off, Hussey drives on the front foot towards the fielder at mid-off
poor line, on the pads, Hussey glances in front of Bishoo at short fine leg, he scampers after the ball and slides to field it before it reaches the boundary
once again the line is on the pads, this time Hussey glances towards short fine leg's left, Bishoo dives to cut it off
defended on the front foot towards cover
Hussey strides forward and fluently drives a length ball through cover
he hits the pad as Bailey pushes forward to defend, the offbreak hit him outside the line of the stumps
defended on the back foot
played off the back foot towards square leg
Bailey moves forward and defends towards the bowler
Bailey stays in his crease and plays the ball with the spin to midwicket
comes forward this time and drives to long-on to ensure it isn't a maiden over

edged and caught! The ball was ordinary, apart from the extra bounce that caused the edge. Russell pitched short and wide, but Baiey top-edged the cut because it bounced a bit more, Baugh took an easy catch to end what was a promising partnership for Australia
pushedoff the front foot to get off the mark right away, a single through cover

caught down the leg side and the umpire Brathwaite gives it out after a long thought! Russel pitched short of a length and Hussey tried to pull, the ball was too close to the body and he was cramped for room, he ended up edging it to the keeper. Russel and Baugh appealed confidently and eventually the finger went up. Hussey did not review it so he must have edged it
A short of a length ball gets big on Wade who defends awkwardly
a short ball and the batsman lets it go
good length angling across the right-hander, left alone by the batsman
nudged off the pads towards square leg
slightly short from Narine and Hussey pulls to deep square leg
defended on the front foot towards point
bowled quicker outside off stump, Wade lets it pass
defended on the back foot to forward short leg
Wade moves forward and defends
good length close to off stump, Hussey stays in his crease and shoulders arms
good length on off stump this time, Hussey has to defend to cover
that's a sharp short ball, Hussey bends his knees and lets it pass
Charles is back at third man and makes a fine diving save to stop a fierce cut from Hussey
good length outside off, Hussey blocks from his crease
played off the back foot towards cover
played off the pads behind square
the quicker ball but it's a bit short outside off, Hussey waits and cuts it past short third man
defended on the front foot
tossed up, Hussey moves forward to take it on the full and whips through midwicket
defended on the front foot
quicker ball pushed across the left-hander, Wade tries to cut but is beaten
short of a length angling into the right-hander, Hussey jumps back and blocks
played towards mid-on, the fielder at midwicket cuts it off
a supremely directed bouncer, Hussey has to way a long way to avoid it
that's only a bit short but Hussey moves back quickly to pull the ball into the gap on the deep midwicket boundary
full delivery angling into the pads, Hussey clips to deep backward square
Wade tries to cut a good length ball that angles across him and is beaten
slides down leg side with his first ball
pulled through square leg for a single
a bit short and Wade cuts off the back foot through point
turned off the pad on the front foot towards square leg
cut from the crease towards backward point
a full delivery, driven to cover
cut off the back foot through backward point

a confident appeal from West Indies after Wade fends at a short of a length delivery that angles across him from over the wicket and is beaten, they thought there might have been an edge, but they do not review the not-out decision
Wade chases a wide ball outside off and gets beaten while trying to cut
Wade jumps and tries to fend a superb short ball and nearly gloves it to the keeper, quick, hostile bowling from Russell
fuller and wide outside off, Wade moves forward and tries to cover drive but can't connect, that's a harsh call from the umpire
short of a length and straight, Wade short-arm pulls in front of square
he's hit this well, pulling a short ball that sits up through midwicket, he hit that from around off stump and connected superbly
Wade moves forward and chases a fuller and wider ball outside off, he gets beaten on the expansive cover drive
played off the pads through square leg
driven to long on for a single
defended on the front foot
Wade strides forward and blocks
punched off the back foot through point
Hussey moves back and plays the ball towards long-on
short of a length and straight, Hussey defends
steered off the back foot through point for a single
good length and straight, defended back to the bowler
played back towards Sammy once again
full with width outside off, Wade lays into it and cover drives with power to the boundary
Pollard's dropped a catch at backward point! Wade moved forward and played the square drive, slicing it in the air and straight to Pollard, that was an absolute sitter
defended on the front foot
swept down on one knee behind square
short ball and Hussey pulls into the gap on the deep square leg boundary
this time he uses the pace and width outside off to steer the ball to the third man boundary
played off the pads behind square
driven to long-on for a single
short of a length outside off, Hussey tries to cut and is beaten
played towards midwicket
Wade stands in his crease and cuts the length ball from outside off towards deep point
Hussey cuts from close to off stump towards third man
full ball angling across the left-hander, driven to cover
Wade jumps up and tries to swat a ball through the off side but he mis-times it
length, outside off and dabbed to point
wide of the crease, short ball, looping in towards Hussey - it's nowhere near quick enough and the batsman muscles it in front of deep midwicket
another long-hop, which Hussey pulls through square leg this time. Pollard's dobblers are being given the treatment
length, wide of off, cut in front of point but a diving stop prevents a single
on the stumps, pushed into the gap at short midwicket
length, rolls his fingers over the ball and Wade pushes into the off side
length ball, strikes Hussey on the pads but Sammy's muted appeal is turned down
drops a tad shorter, pushed towards cover
wide of off stump and driven through a gap at cover
angled into the right hander, worked into the on side
pitched up a bit more and Hussey drives to the cover sweeper
full delivery, outside off, chipped over the infield through cover
length, outside off, guided down to third man
back of a length, on the legs and Wade dribbles it round the corner
bangs it in, towards the body, Hussey hops back and gets a leading edge that pops short on to the wicket
short and wide, Hussey needs no invitation to slap a cut shot dismissively behind point
room outside off and Hussey steers the ball behind point - that brings up a doughty fifty

gone! Wade slogs high into the St Lucia sky and is caught at long-off! It was a pitched up delivery, outside off but Wade could only get underneath it. After his contribution with the bat, Pollard has secured a key breakthrough with his loping medium pace. This will be known as Pollard's ODI in years to come
length, outside off and cut to point
slightly shorter, Lee guides it down to third man

gone! Or is he? Hussey slogged to deep midwicket - but it had been called a no-ball! There were too many fielders in the ring, apparently Hussey uncharacteristically let rip at a short ball, scooping it into the deep, where a diving catch was well-taken
length, Lee misses with a prod outside off
driven to cover
outside off, pushed towards cover again
squeezed out square - good diving stop at point but the throw concedes a misfield
tossed up, Lee smothers it outside off
on the stumps, blocked
room outside off and Lee steers it past the slip for a four to third man
flighted, on the stumps, Lee defends
quicker delivery, Lee edges on to his pads in front of leg stump
on the stumps, towards leg, Lee misses and ball hits him on the pad
full-length delivery, punched down the ground to long-on
length ball, Lee defends on the back foot in front of the stumps
shorter delivery, Lee knocks it towards point
back of a length, fired in a Lee's body, he takes his bottom hand of the bat as he jabs it into the leg side
pitched up and Hussey steps out, drives to long-on
length, on the pads and flicked round the corner to short leg
length ball, on the stumps and spinning to leg, Hussey nudges on the back foot to short leg
tossed up and struck hard to midwicket ... Samuels makes the stop but can't prevent the batsmen stealing a run
tossed up on the stumps, blocked
flatter, outside off, Lee leans out and prods square
leg-stump line, the ball cannons out square off the pad
bouncer, well-directed and following Hussey as he swayed back in his crease
pitched up and driven in the air over mid-off - not a clean connection and its collected before the boundary

ouch! Roach bowls a beamer that strikes Lee flush on the glove. It's a no-ball and Roach goes down the wicket to apologise ... Lee jerked away from that like he'd been scalded. He dropped his bat as the ball struck his left hand, then dropped to his knees. He initially walked away from Roach, as if to compose himself - but he hasn't directed any ill-feeling towards the bowler. And he'll continue to bat ...
and Roach follows it up with a short ball that Lee keeps away from his ribs by nudging into the leg side. All's fair in cricket and war

gone, bowled him! It was a length delivery, quick and ducked in just a little, beating Hussey's drive and clattering into the top of off stump. That could be the curtain call for Australia. They still need 99 to win with just three wickets in hand
first ball to McKay is back of a length, and defended on the back foot
a quick bouncer, which the batsman steps away from
tossed up on the stumps, defended
outside off, driven past cover by Lee
flighted in, McKay pushes forward outside off and is hit on the pad - but he was outside off stump
again tossed up outside off and spinning back into the pad, this one might have been going down leg
slightly quicker, edged on to his pads
full, outside off, driven to the close fielder
full, quick and Lee inside-edges to the fine leg rope for four
shot! pitched up again and Lee steps back to blammo a four through extra-cover
three in a row! Roach is striving for the yorker but it's not quite full enough and Lee spears it through cover. He's taking out his frustrations from Roach's last over
this time his picks up the ball and deposits it back over long-on! That was a ferocious hit, a huge windmilling swing of the arms and the ball flies over the boundary
Roach hits back with a bouncer and Lee is forced to curtail his aggression
he connects again with another almighty thrash, flat-batting a six over deep midwicket. Lee the gunslinger is going to go down in a blaze! That's 24 off the over!
length, on the stumps and McKay fiddles it into the leg side
pitched up wide of the stumps and Lee can't get his flashing blade under this one, squirting the ball out towards point
line and length, Lee gets behind this one
length, outside off and Lee swings so hard he almost comes off his feet - but the ball flies straight to cover
Lee smokes another massive six, into the stands over extra-cover! Bravo pitched it up into the slot and the batsman rocked back and creamed it into the crowd. Lee is batting incredibly here ...
Lee backs away again and Bravo slings it wide of off, the batsman unable to connect
back of a length and McKay loops it to square leg
full, slower, out the back of the hand and Lee is forced to jam down on it
full-speed yorker this time, following Lee down the leg side, cramping him for space and he can't make a proper connection with the bat
rolls his fingers over the ball, Lee smites it from outside off stump over cover for a couple
full and slightly wide, driven with a flourish but straight to cover
length ball, pushed on the back foot to short third man - a good over form Russell, just putting the lid on Lee's fiery retribution
full, on the legs and swiped down to the rope at fine leg. Lee's just a couple more slogs from fifty ...
on the stumps, swings the arms and clips a length ball through square leg
well-directed bouncer, beating an enthusiastic swish

the slower ball does for McKay, who spoons the ball off the bottom of the bat to long-on. He didn't pick the change of pace, tried to break a window but was well off with his timing - Pollard taking a comfortable catch
back of a length, dropped short on the leg side and they dash through for one
over the wicket, length ball angled into the left-handed Doherty - he gets solidly behind it and defends
bouncer, directed at the batsman, who swings and misses
smashed down the ground and Lee goes to fifty with a six! Another piece of clean hitting that would make Kieron Pollard proud!
another one goes the distance! This time straight down the ground, rather than over long-on. Holy Moly
pitched right up and Lee manages to keep the ball out and scramble one to mid-on
length, outside off and Doherty plays and misses
on the stumps and flicked to short fine leg
flighted on the stumps, Doherty nibbles it back to the bowler
tossed up, on leg stump, spinning across and beats the outside edge

full ball, chipped to short cover and gone! It wasn't quite there for the drive, Doherty was reaching for the ball and ended up steering it in the air on the off side, the captain Darren Sammy taking a smart catch
middle and leg doosra, Hilfenhaus defends in front of his stumps
given some air outside off, spinning back inside the bat as Hilfenhaus goes to leave
dragged down the leg side
on the stumps, spinning across into the pad but sliding down leg
back of a length, Lee swings and gets a bottom edge that flies to short leg
another bouncer, swinging across the batsman, who misses with a flailing bat
more chin music - though it goes some way above Lee's head, let alone his chin. That's called wide

gives it the old heave-ho again but this time Lee can't clear long-off. That's it, West Indies have won! Roach removes Lee by legitimate means - though he probably regrets winding him up in the first place. A heroic innings from Lee, his best score in ODIs, but the task proved beyond him and his team-mates
